definitions.definition: The act of abducing or abducting ; a drawing apart; the movement which separates a limb or other part from the axis , or middle line, of the body.
A syllogism or form of argument in which the major premise is evident , but the minor is only probable .
The wrongful , and usually forcible , carrying off of a human being.

main_definition: Leading away; a carrying away. [from early 17 century.]
secondary_definitions: ( anatomy ) The act of abducing or abducting ; a drawing apart; the movement which separates a limb or other part from the axis , or middle line, of the body. [from mid-17 century.]
( logic ) A syllogism or form of argument in which the major premise is evident , but the minor is only probable . [from late 17 century.]
( law ) The wrongful , and usually forcible , carrying off of a human being. [from mid-18 century.]
